    "content": "# Tango x UNFI â€” Brain\n\n**Target:** $10,000/month | **Current:** $3,400/month | **Gap:** $6,600\n**Weight:** 25%\n\n---\n\n## My Current Understanding\n\nUNFI is Tango's wholesale distribution channel, getting us into grocery stores via two distribution centers: Moreno Valley (SoPac/LA) and Hudson Valley (Northeast/NYC). We're in the UpNext emerging brands program.\n\n**Status:** SoPac is growing +516% YoY. Northeast needs SKU expansion (no Mango). Endless Aisle paperwork blocking new store access.\n\n---\n\n## Goals\n\n| Timeframe | Goal |\n|-----------|------|\n| **This Month** | Get to $10K/month ASAP |\n| **12 Months** | Graduate from UpNext ($300K annual) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Metrics\n\n| Metric | Current | Target | Gap |\n|--------|---------|--------|-----|\n| Monthly Revenue | $3,400 | $10,000 | $6,600 |\n| SoPac YoY | +516% | Maintain | --- |\n| Northeast YoY | -9% | +20% | Needs Mango |\n| Store Count | ~50 | 200+ | +150 |\n\n---\n\n## Distribution Centers\n\n| DC | Location | Vendor # | SKUs |\n|----|----------|----------|------|\n| Moreno Valley | Riverside, CA | L-086208 | Hot, Mild, Mango |\n| Hudson Valley | Montgomery, NY | 79667 | Hot, Mild |\n\n**NOT in UNFI:** Truffle, Thai, Sriracha\n\n---\n\n## Blockers\n\n| What's Blocked | Why | Unblock Action |\n|---------------|-----|----------------|\n| Northeast SKU expansion | Waiting on John Lawson | Follow up (emailed Jan 20) |\n| New store access | Endless Aisle forms incomplete | Complete 8 forms |\n| UpNext status | Almost dropped May 2025 | Monthly check-ins with Brittney |\n\n---\n\n## Pipeline\n\n### High Level\n- [ ] Follow up with John Lawson â†’ SKU expansion to Northeast (Jan 27 follow-up)\n- [ ] Complete Endless Aisle paperwork â†’ 8 forms blocking new store access\n- [ ] Monthly check-in with Brittney â†’ UpNext status, show growth\n\n### MOR (Moreno Valley) â€” New Store Targets\n- [ ] **Erewhon** â†’ Email Lauren Martinez (warm lead, 12 stores) â€” NOTE: Erewhon uses KeHE, not UNFI\n- [ ] **Bristol Farms / Lazy Acres** â†’ Research buyer + submit RangeMe (20 stores)\n- [ ] **Gelson's** â†’ Research buyer contact (27 stores, premium LA positioning)\n- [ ] **Sprouts** â†’ Research buyer contact (400+ stores)\n- [ ] **Mother's Market** â†’ Research buyer contact (11 stores)\n\n### HVA (Hudson Valley) â€” New Store Targets\n- [ ] **Wegmans** â†’ Research buyer contact (50 stores)\n- [ ] **ShopRite (Wakefern)** â†’ Research buyer contact (300 stores)\n- [ ] **DeCicco's** â†’ Research buyer contact (14 stores)\n- [ ] **Fairway Market** â†’ Research buyer contact (5 stores, NYC gourmet)\n- [ ] **Stew Leonard's** â†’ Research buyer contact (7 stores, CT/NY)\n\n---\n\n## What We've Learned\n\n### Confirmed Wins\n- **LA is the growth engine**: SoPac +516% YoY vs Northeast -9% YoY\n- **Top LA performers**: Venice +396%, Downtown LA +1,201%, Glendale +364%, Santa Barbara +792%\n- **Mild is growing**: +20.6% YoY at Whole Foods\n- **Mango is trending**: +63% YoY â€” smallest but fastest growing\n- **Already in UNFI**: Makes new store outreach seamless (\"We're already in UNFI, fulfillment is seamless\")\n\n### Confirmed Failures\n- **Truffle, Thai, Sriracha not in UNFI**: Can't sell what's not in the system\n- **Hudson Valley doesn't carry Mango**: Limits Northeast growth\n- **NYC outreach without SKU expansion is limited**: Hot + Mild only in HV\n\n### Clarified (Jan 2026)\n- **Endless Aisle â‰  adding new products** â€” It's supplier paperwork/catalog updates for existing warehouse SKUs\n- **Endless Aisle is regional** â€” Products only visible to stores served by the DC where stocked\n- **To add new SKUs to UNFI** â€” Requires separate pitch to rep, approval, item setup docs, inventory shipment\n- **Food safety audit workaround works** â€” Promissory notes accepted (done 2017, 2024, now 2026)\n- **Sriracha 6-pack UPC not registered in GS1** â€” Would need to create before UNFI submission\n\n### Historical Context\n- Aug 2022: Erewhon said \"everyone loves the taste\" but rejected on packaging design\n- Sep 2025: Re-reached Erewhon with new packaging, got routed to vendor portal\n- May 2025: Almost dropped from UpNext â€” reversed after response\n- Dan was behind The Truffleist brand (NE Whole Foods run) â€” relevant for truffle velocity proof\n\n---\n\n## What We've Tried\n\n| Date | Action | Result | Learning |\n|------|--------|--------|----------|\n| Jan 20, 2026 | Emailed John Lawson re: full lineup | Awaiting response | Follow up Jan 27 |\n| Sep 2025 | Re-contacted Erewhon | Routed to vendor portal | Portal needs Non-GMO cert (may be flexible) |\n| Aug 2022 | Initial Erewhon outreach | Taste loved, packaging rejected | New packaging addresses this |\n| May 2025 | Responded to UpNext termination notice | Decision reversed | Brittney is invested, need to show growth |\n\n---\n\n## Cold Email Template\n\n**Structure:** Hook â†’ Proof â†’ CTA\n\n```\nSubject: [Chain Name] + Tango â€” Premium Hot Sauce (Already in UNFI)\n\nHi [First Name],\n\n[HOOK: 1-2 sentences specific to them]\n\nI'm reaching out because Tango Hot Sauce is a perfect fit for [Chain Name]'s\n[premium/health-conscious/foodie] customer base.\n\n[PROOF]\n- Already distributed through UNFI (Moreno Valley DC) â€” no new vendor setup needed\n- Currently in XX Whole Foods locations across Southern California\n- Carrot-based, keto-friendly, no sugar added\n\n[CTA]\nWould you be open to trying a sample? I can have a set delivered this week.\n\nBest,\nDan Frieber\nFounder, Tango Hot Sauce\n```\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What's John Lawson's actual decision-making timeline for SKU expansion?\n- Is Erewhon's Non-GMO requirement hard or flexible?\n- Should we prioritize chain HQ outreach or independent store blitz first?\n- What's the right demo strategy â€” which stores, how many per month?\n- When does Brittney expect us to hit graduation thresholds?\n- **Should we get into KeHE?** Erewhon uses KeHE. Would open that door but adds distributor complexity.\n\n---\n\n## Key Contacts\n\n| Name | Role | Status | Last Contact |\n|------|------|--------|-------------|\n| John Lawson | Whole Foods buyer | Awaiting response | Jan 20, 2026 |\n| Lauren Martinez | Erewhon Brand Mgmt | Warm lead | Sep 2025 |\n| Brittney Langlois | UNFI UpNext SDM (blanglois@unfi.com) | Monthly check-ins | May 2025 |\n\n---\n\n## Endless Aisle Paperwork Status\n\n**Location:** `/tango/distribution/unfi/endless aisle/`\n\n| Step | Form | Status |\n|------|------|--------|\n| 1 | Supplier Checklist | Done (existing supplier info) |\n| 2 | W-9 | Need fresh copy |\n| 3 | New Supplier Application | Fill with existing vendor info |\n| 4 | ACH Form | Need banking info |\n| 5-10 | Item Setup Documents | Use Moreno Valley specs |\n| 11 | Insurance COI | Get from RSC |\n| 12 | Food Safety Audit | Done (promissory note) |\n| 13 | Quality Assurance Agreement | Review and sign |\n\n---\n\n## Intel (Time-Sensitive)\n\n| Date | Finding | Source | Expires |\n|------|---------|--------|---------|\n| Jan 22, 2026 | Erewhon uses KeHE, NOT UNFI â€” UNFI distribution doesn't help here | KeHE press release | Ongoing |\n| Jan 22, 2026 | Bristol Farms uses RangeMe â€” submit there + direct outreach | Research | Ongoing |\n| Jan 22, 2026 | Gelson's = premium LA positioning â€” fits Tango, same UNFI DC | Research | Ongoing |\n| Jan 21, 2026 | Erewhon opening West Hollywood Feb 2026 | WestsideCurrent | Feb 2026 |\n| Jan 21, 2026 | Erewhon opening Glendale May 2026 | WestsideCurrent | May 2026 |\n| Jan 21, 2026 | Erewhon opening Thousand Oaks July 2026 | Conejo Valley Guide | July 2026 |\n| Jan 21, 2026 | Erewhon opening NYC flagship late 2026 â€” first East Coast location | Modern Retail | Q4 2026 |\n| Jan 21, 2026 | Erewhon vendor requirements: Non-GMO + USDA Organic preferred, no refined sugar | Modern Retail | Ongoing |\n\n---\n\n*Migrated from Notion (Tango x UNFI) â€” Feb 17, 2026*\n",
